cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and language models. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the effectiveness of a new model on benchmark datasets. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper introduces a new model that combines different techniques to improve performance on NLP tasks. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses a pre-trained neural language model (BERT) and introduces a new model that leverages its structure. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the importance of untangling data-specific semantics from general language structure, which is a concept that can also apply to computer vision tasks.
